Subject: [PATCH 4/4] powerpc/85xx: Enabling CONFIG_PPC_CLOCK from FlexCAN

Enabling clk_interface infrastructure from FlexCAN itself which
otherwise we have to enable via  CPM
Signed-off-by: Bhaskar Upadhaya <Bhaskar.Upadhaya@freescale.com>

[Kevin: Original patch taken from FSL NODPAA SDK 1.0
QorIQ-NONDPAA-SDK-V1-20110429_ltib.iso]

Integrated-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/can/Kconfig |    4 ++++
 1 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/can/Kconfig b/drivers/net/can/Kconfig
index f9d93cd..109e0d6 100644
--- a/drivers/net/can/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/can/Kconfig
@@ -91,8 +91,12 @@ config HAVE_CAN_FLEXCAN
 config CAN_FLEXCAN_PPC
 	tristate "Support for FLEXCAN drivers on powerpc"
 	depends on CAN_DEV && HAVE_CAN_FLEXCAN
+	select PPC_CLOCK
 	---help---
 	  Say Y here if you want support for Freescale FlexCAN.
+	  Flexcan Module is implementing the CAN Protocol
+	  version 2.0
+
 
 source "drivers/net/can/mscan/Kconfig"
 
